parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sinks to the floor
the vehicle fails to slow down or stop
multiple warning lights on the dashboard (e.g.
malfunction indicator light
brake light
ABS light
traction control
electronic stability control
Forward collision system failure)
loss of motive power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The absence of the park assist sensor can increase the risk of accidents or damage to the vehicle, as the driver may not be aware of obstacles when parking or maneuvering in tight spaces.
symptoms: The vehicle is missing the park assist sensor
which is supposed to be installed as standard or optional equipment; the sensor is not functioning; the vehicle does not alert the driver of obstacles when parking or maneuvering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty transmission solenoid can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to erratic shifting, slipping, or failure to engage gears, which can result in loss of vehicle control, accidents, or strand the driver.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting
the transmission fails to engage into gear
the transmission shifts erratically
the vehicle experiences sudden acceleration or deceleration
the transmission warning light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty TCM can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to erratic shifting, slipping, or failure to engage gears, which can result in loss of vehicle control, accidents, or strand the driver.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting
the transmission fails to engage into gear
the transmission shifts erratically
the vehicle experiences sudden acceleration or deceleration
the transmission warning light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Camera System and Sensor Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The absence or malfunction of the rear camera system and sensors can increase the risk of accidents or injuries while reversing, as the driver may not be aware of obstacles or pedestrians behind the vehicle.
symptoms: The rear camera system does not display an image
the rear camera system displays a distorted or unclear image
the rear sensors do not provide audible or visual warnings of obstacles
the rear sensors provide false or late warnings of obstacles.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Missing Safety Feature Updates
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or failure to provide promised safety feature updates can leave vehicles without critical safety features, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle is missing promised safety features
the vehicle's safety features are not functioning as intended
the manufacturer has failed to provide updates or repairs to address safety concerns.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty fuel pump module can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, decelerate, and fail to accelerate, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
decelerates
and fails to accelerate
the check engine warning light is illuminated
the transmission shifts into neutral unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission shifting into neutral without warning can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission shifts into neutral unexpectedly
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle decelerates
the check engine warning light is illuminated.
